<%- include("partials/header") -%>

<section class="lightSection">
  <div>
    <h1 class="title">Etiquette & Code of Conduct</h1>

    <div class="mb-3">
      <div class="swingvasion-box">
        <div class="swingvasion-details">
          <div class="m-4">
            <ul style="font-size: 18px">
              <li>
                If you have any questions throughout the event, our crew at the
                front desk will be happy to help.
              </li>
              <li>
                This is an alcohol-free event, and glass containers are not
                permitted inside the venue. Feel free to bring water, juice, or
                other non-alcoholic drinks in a sealable bottle. If you do have
                a spill, please let a crew member know or help clean it up
                promptly so nobody ends up slipping or standing in it.
              </li>
              <li>
                If you're feeling unwell, we ask that you stay home - look after
                yourself and help us take care of our other attendees. There
                will always be another opportunity to dance!
              </li>
              <li>
                Please keep bags and personal belongings tucked away under
                tables or against the wall so that walkways and dance spaces
                remain clear.
              </li>
              <li>
                Everyone is here to learn, and we all learn at our own pace.
                Please avoid giving unsolicited advice or feedback, both during
                workshops and on the social floor. The exception, of course, is
                if you are feeling unsafe or have been hurt.
              </li>
              <li>
                We're lucky to have dancers joining us from all over New Zealand
                and beyond. Take the opportunity to meet new people and ask lots
                of different people to dance.
              </li>
              <li>
                Please be mindful of your partner's comfort and always respect
                their boundaries. There are many different factors that
                influence what someone is comfortable with.
              </li>
              <li>
                You're welcome to dance in whichever role you choose - lead,
                follow, or both!
              </li>
              <li>
                We believe strongly in a culture of consent. Please ask someone
                to dance, and don't take it personally if they decline. A simple
                "No thank you" is a complete and acceptable response, and no
                explanation is ever required.
              </li>
              <li>
                We want Swingvasion to be a safe, welcoming, and inclusive
                environment for everyone. We have zero tolerance for behaviour
                that makes others feel unsafe or unwelcome, including
                inappropriate or sexual comments or jokes, unwanted physical
                contact, repeatedly pursuing someone after they've declined a
                dance, or discrimination of any kind.
              </li>
              <li>
                If you experience or witness behaviour that concerns you, please
                speak to a member of the crew. Reports will be handled
                respectfully, discreetly, and confidentially by the appropriate
                Swingvasion staff. Where behaviour compromises someone's safety
                or the event's code of conduct, staff will intervene. Depending
                on the circumstances, individuals may be asked to leave the
                event immediately and without refund.
              </li>
              <li>Most importantly – have fun!!</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<%- include("partials/footer") -%>
